1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:42,338
(Three years ago)

3
00:01:48,168 --> 00:01:49,088
Done disinfecting here?

4
00:01:49,088 --> 00:01:49,808
Yes.

5
00:02:05,368 --> 00:02:06,127
Who is it?

6
00:02:06,648 --> 00:02:07,847
Hello, is this unit 2602?

7
00:02:07,847 --> 00:02:08,727
Your supplies are

8
00:02:08,727 --> 00:02:09,887
in the elevator.

9
00:02:09,887 --> 00:02:10,687
Please take them.

10
00:02:11,248 --> 00:02:11,847
Thank you.

11
00:02:12,488 --> 00:02:13,007
Wait.

12
00:02:13,648 --> 00:02:14,928
The light here isn't working.

13
00:02:14,928 --> 00:02:16,167
Can you check for me?

14
00:02:17,528 --> 00:02:18,407
I can fix it for you.

15
00:02:18,407 --> 00:02:20,208
But please take proper precautions.

16
00:02:21,007 --> 00:02:21,528
Okay.

17
00:02:27,488 --> 00:02:28,928
When did you move in?

18
00:02:29,808 --> 00:02:30,847
About a year ago.

19
00:02:31,248 --> 00:02:32,088
Really?

20
00:02:32,127 --> 00:02:33,768
Why haven't I seen you before?

21
00:02:34,088 --> 00:02:35,407
Did you rent or buy?

22
00:02:35,928 --> 00:02:36,768
I bought it.

23
00:02:36,768 --> 00:02:37,768
Bought it yourself?

24
00:02:40,287 --> 00:02:41,407
That's really impressive.

25
00:02:41,768 --> 00:02:43,488
The apartments here are expensive.

26
00:02:44,687 --> 00:02:46,127
I bought the 90-square-meter unit,

27
00:02:46,328 --> 00:02:47,928
so the total price was lower.

28
00:02:48,127 --> 00:02:50,847
No matter how big it is,
you bought it through your own efforts.

29
00:02:51,127 --> 00:02:53,808
It's tough for you young people trying
to make it on your own

30
00:02:53,808 --> 00:02:55,167
in Guangzhou.

31
00:02:58,007 --> 00:02:58,847
You're younger.

32
00:02:58,847 --> 00:02:59,687
You said I'm young?

33
00:02:59,687 --> 00:03:00,808
I have an old soul.

34
00:03:02,768 --> 00:03:03,727
Almost done. Check it.

35
00:03:04,328 --> 00:03:04,687
Okay.

36
00:03:10,368 --> 00:03:11,208
It's on.

37
00:03:13,287 --> 00:03:14,607
Thank you so much.

38
00:03:14,928 --> 00:03:17,167
I called the property management,
and no one answered.

39
00:03:17,488 --> 00:03:18,208
Have some coffee.

40
00:03:18,208 --> 00:03:18,847
I made it.

41
00:03:21,127 --> 00:03:21,928
I'll stay away.

42
00:03:22,127 --> 00:03:22,808
Over there.

43
00:03:30,007 --> 00:03:31,368
I found you in the group chat.

44
00:03:31,368 --> 00:03:32,127
I add you.

45
00:03:32,808 --> 00:03:35,368
Okay, I appreciate the gesture.

46
00:03:35,368 --> 00:03:37,407
But maybe skip the coffee.

47
00:03:38,048 --> 00:03:38,768
It's fine.

48
00:03:38,768 --> 00:03:39,567
Take the cup back

49
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:40,368
and drink it later.

50
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:53,192
(Big Little Lies, Trade Offs,
Pros and Cons, Mask)

51
00:03:55,144 --> 00:03:57,844
=Episode 10=
(Lies)

52
00:03:57,968 --> 00:03:59,208
Don't drink so much next time.

53
00:04:00,687 --> 00:04:02,768
There are no meetings
in Hangzhou these two days.

54
00:04:03,328 --> 00:04:04,648
Dong Yue lied to you.

55
00:04:07,088 --> 00:04:08,847
Last time, we both carried someone out.

56
00:04:08,847 --> 00:04:09,887
It was Mr. Xu, right?

57
00:04:09,887 --> 00:04:10,528
Remember that?

58
00:04:11,088 --> 00:04:13,847
Have you seen Xu since?

59
00:04:14,887 --> 00:04:15,968
Yes, once.

60
00:04:16,528 --> 00:04:17,727
To hand over clients.

61
00:04:21,807 --> 00:04:22,407
What's wrong?

62
00:04:23,528 --> 00:04:24,167
What?

63
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:29,367
You men are good at lying.

64
00:04:29,648 --> 00:04:30,328
What do you mean?

65
00:04:31,008 --> 00:04:33,167
Just tell me

66
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:35,927
you're here to see the big boss.

67
00:04:36,328 --> 00:04:39,208
You even claimed you had
a meeting in Hangzhou during the day

68
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:41,167
and arrived in Shanghai at night.

69
00:04:41,487 --> 00:04:47,047
You said you were only
handing over clients with Xu?

70
00:04:49,008 --> 00:04:51,008
You're such a liar.

71
00:04:51,768 --> 00:04:54,607
Why do you men
always treat women like fools?

72
00:04:56,167 --> 00:04:57,727
Can't you live without lying?

73
00:04:57,888 --> 00:04:58,888
Haven't you lied?

74
00:04:58,888 --> 00:05:00,047
What lie have I told?

75
00:05:00,047 --> 00:05:01,888
You came to Shanghai
for cosmetic injections?

76
00:05:01,888 --> 00:05:04,088
Aren't you here to meet Barry
with your husband?

77
00:05:04,448 --> 00:05:06,247
Cosmetic injections? Who'd believe that?

78
00:05:06,247 --> 00:05:07,047
Believe it or not.

79
00:05:07,047 --> 00:05:08,287
I really can't believe it.

80
00:05:08,607 --> 00:05:09,607
You don't need to.

81
00:05:09,607 --> 00:05:11,208
At least make your lies convincing.

82
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:12,927
You can only fool yourself with that.

83
00:05:13,287 --> 00:05:15,008
Cosmetic injections? Am I a fool to you?

84
00:05:18,927 --> 00:05:19,927
Hello, ma'am.

85
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:21,328
Are you okay?

86
00:05:23,008 --> 00:05:23,888
Are you drunk?

87
00:05:24,208 --> 00:05:25,167
I'm fine.

88
00:05:25,328 --> 00:05:26,047
Your room number?

89
00:05:26,047 --> 00:05:27,167
I'll let someone escort you.

90
00:05:29,568 --> 00:05:30,328
What's wrong?

91
00:05:31,008 --> 00:05:31,968
She seems drunk.

92
00:05:33,768 --> 00:05:34,328
Are you okay?

93
00:05:58,888 --> 00:05:59,528
Take it easy.

94
00:06:06,888 --> 00:06:07,328
Easy.

95
00:06:20,607 --> 00:06:21,287
You can go.

96
00:06:23,287 --> 00:06:26,407
Okay, then drink some honey water.

97
00:06:26,407 --> 00:06:27,367
It'll soothe you.

98
00:06:32,128 --> 00:06:32,528
I'm off.

99
00:06:39,847 --> 00:06:40,360
You okay?

100
00:06:40,968 --> 00:06:42,688
Should I call your husband to come?

101
00:07:00,528 --> 00:07:01,287
Get me tissue.

102
00:07:01,727 --> 00:07:02,528
Get me some tissue.

103
00:07:07,528 --> 00:07:08,208
You run a fever.

104
00:07:15,528 --> 00:07:16,648
Your phone has been ringing.

105
00:07:16,888 --> 00:07:17,807
Might be an emergency.

106
00:07:18,128 --> 00:07:19,167
Enter the password.

107
00:07:32,448 --> 00:07:33,047
Alright.

108
00:07:43,128 --> 00:07:43,927
I'll get the meds.

109
00:08:10,927 --> 00:08:12,568
(Don't pity on her.)

110
00:08:13,167 --> 00:08:14,407
(This is a golden opportunity!)

111
00:08:14,727 --> 00:08:16,768
(If the company finds out
her husband cheated,)

112
00:08:16,847 --> 00:08:18,287
(it'll destroy her completely.)

113
00:08:18,568 --> 00:08:19,448
(I'll get rid of her.)

114
00:08:19,727 --> 00:08:20,727
(Why am I hesitating?)

115
00:08:20,727 --> 00:08:22,128
Sir, here's your medicine.

116
00:08:22,568 --> 00:08:23,047
Thanks.

117
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:23,648
Not at all.

118
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:24,927
Wait.

119
00:08:24,927 --> 00:08:28,167
I wanted to ask,
was Ms. Zhao checked in alone?

120
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:29,727
Yes, only her.

121
00:08:30,448 --> 00:08:31,128
Thanks.

122
00:08:31,128 --> 00:08:31,528
It's okay.

123
00:08:37,127 --> 00:08:37,928
38.8 degrees.

124
00:08:40,367 --> 00:08:41,048
Take medicine.

125
00:08:50,247 --> 00:08:51,487
I need to use the restroom.

126
00:09:17,727 --> 00:09:18,527
What are you doing?

127
00:09:19,328 --> 00:09:20,127
On a business trip.

128
00:09:20,968 --> 00:09:22,367
I know that.

129
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:23,647
I'm asking where you are.

130
00:09:23,887 --> 00:09:25,007
In a hotel room.

131
00:09:25,007 --> 00:09:27,088
My colleague is sick,
just took the medicine.

132
00:09:27,808 --> 00:09:28,088
What?

133
00:09:28,088 --> 00:09:29,568
Shen Xing, come have a drink!

134
00:09:29,568 --> 00:09:30,408
No, wait.

135
00:09:30,847 --> 00:09:31,367
Show me.

136
00:09:34,328 --> 00:09:36,247
Not medicine, but the person.

137
00:09:36,247 --> 00:09:37,767
Show me your colleague.

138
00:09:37,968 --> 00:09:39,847
No, she has a right to privacy.

139
00:09:40,007 --> 00:09:41,328
What's there to hide?

140
00:09:41,727 --> 00:09:42,487
Shen Xing!

141
00:09:42,487 --> 00:09:43,487
Shen Xing, come drink!

142
00:09:44,007 --> 00:09:44,928
Coming.

143
00:09:45,127 --> 00:09:46,247
I have to go, bye.

144
00:09:48,007 --> 00:09:48,808
Coming!

145
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:00,847
Sorry.

146
00:10:08,408 --> 00:10:10,408
Didn't expect you to tell the truth.

147
00:10:11,568 --> 00:10:12,568
I have nothing to hide.

148
00:10:18,448 --> 00:10:19,487
Put this on

149
00:10:20,127 --> 00:10:20,968
and it'll soothe you.

150
00:10:25,127 --> 00:10:25,647
Thanks.

151
00:10:33,448 --> 00:10:35,368
♪Too much of shame♪

152
00:10:35,714 --> 00:10:38,510
♪To waste it crying♪

153
00:10:40,968 --> 00:10:42,888
♪Leave all behind you♪

154
00:10:42,888 --> 00:10:45,168
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

155
00:10:45,288 --> 00:10:47,517
♪You know how far you've gone♪

156
00:10:47,652 --> 00:10:49,928
♪In the fire you rise again♪

157
00:10:50,114 --> 00:10:52,474
♪You made it through the worst♪

158
00:10:52,612 --> 00:10:54,816
♪The best is yet to come♪

159
00:10:55,059 --> 00:10:57,199
♪The best is yet to come♪

160
00:10:59,901 --> 00:11:01,224
♪Isn't it magical♪

161
00:11:01,224 --> 00:11:01,832
♪Open the window♪

162
00:11:01,832 --> 00:11:03,110
♪See the beautiful night♪

163
00:11:03,110 --> 00:11:04,245
♪I tried hard too♪

164
00:11:04,245 --> 00:11:05,414
♪But ended up with regret♪

165
00:11:05,414 --> 00:11:06,796
♪The clock ticks away♪

166
00:11:06,796 --> 00:11:08,029
♪Relentlessly urging me♪

167
00:11:08,029 --> 00:11:09,020
♪Declined every party♪

168
00:11:09,020 --> 00:11:10,224
♪Living like a compass♪

169
00:11:10,808 --> 00:11:13,448
Can you send me the analysis report
on Chinese whiskey consumption

170
00:11:13,688 --> 00:11:15,367
by 10 AM tomorrow?

171
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,558
♪Pressure upon opening my eyes♪

172
00:11:16,558 --> 00:11:17,843
♪Maybe it fuels me♪

173
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:19,048
♪The meals eaten on time♪

174
00:11:19,048 --> 00:11:20,568
I haven't finished it.

175
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,004
♪Please don't love so hard♪

176
00:11:22,004 --> 00:11:23,140
♪I give up♪

177
00:11:23,448 --> 00:11:24,208
Maybe...

178
00:11:25,123 --> 00:11:26,386
♪On being a hero♪

179
00:11:26,568 --> 00:11:27,408
I'll do it now.

180
00:11:27,808 --> 00:11:28,247
Go ahead.

181
00:11:28,756 --> 00:11:30,835
♪Feels like my mouth is covered♪

182
00:11:30,835 --> 00:11:33,435
♪Silent and unnoticed♪

183
00:11:33,435 --> 00:11:34,984
♪You've poured out♪

184
00:11:34,984 --> 00:11:36,913
♪All your sorrow♪

185
00:11:36,913 --> 00:11:39,303
♪But no one cares at all♪

186
00:11:39,303 --> 00:11:41,700
♪To hear your story♪

187
00:11:51,112 --> 00:11:52,408
(Tao)

188
00:11:52,408 --> 00:11:53,088
Qiao Hailun.

189
00:11:53,887 --> 00:11:54,688
You know what?

190
00:11:55,448 --> 00:11:57,247
You're the dumbest woman I've ever met.

191
00:11:59,048 --> 00:12:01,568
Think you've succeeded
after you latched onto Li Dongming?

192
00:12:02,007 --> 00:12:03,048
Let me tell you.

193
00:12:03,048 --> 00:12:04,328
You're dreaming!

194
00:12:07,847 --> 00:12:08,607
(You know what?)

195
00:12:09,048 --> 00:12:10,527
(In Li Dongming's eyes,)

196
00:12:10,727 --> 00:12:13,208
(you're just a tool. Get it?)

197
00:12:14,328 --> 00:12:16,527
(Working hard during the day
preparing presentations,)

198
00:12:16,607 --> 00:12:18,808
(and working hard at night
even on business trips.)

199
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:21,568
(You crack me up!)

200
00:12:22,012 --> 00:12:23,396
♪How far you've gone♪

201
00:12:24,527 --> 00:12:25,647
(You wretch!)

202
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:28,007
(You deserve it!)

203
00:12:28,328 --> 00:12:30,858
♪The best is yet to come♪

204
00:12:30,858 --> 00:12:33,225
♪The best is yet to come♪

205
00:12:35,784 --> 00:12:37,704
♪Isn't it magical♪

206
00:12:41,968 --> 00:12:42,527
Mr. Dong.

207
00:12:42,847 --> 00:12:44,328
You came straight from the airport?

208
00:12:44,487 --> 00:12:45,887
Yes, back for a meeting.

209
00:12:46,328 --> 00:12:48,088
Make me
a 24th-floor elevator access card.

210
00:12:48,168 --> 00:12:48,928
I've applied.

211
00:12:49,088 --> 00:12:50,088
Okay, just a moment.

212
00:12:54,127 --> 00:12:54,487
Here.

213
00:12:55,727 --> 00:12:56,688
Put this in my office.

214
00:12:56,808 --> 00:12:57,208
Got it.

215
00:12:57,288 --> 00:12:57,688
Thanks.

216
00:13:07,527 --> 00:13:08,247
Peter is waiting.

217
00:13:12,168 --> 00:13:12,568
Sir.

218
00:13:13,647 --> 00:13:15,208
I used to hate milk

219
00:13:15,568 --> 00:13:18,527
until I discovered
adding liquor and ice to it

220
00:13:18,928 --> 00:13:21,208
elevates the taste tenfold.

221
00:13:22,727 --> 00:13:23,688
Make you one?

222
00:13:24,088 --> 00:13:24,727
No, thanks.

223
00:13:25,288 --> 00:13:25,688
It's good.

224
00:13:32,208 --> 00:13:32,968
Down to business.

225
00:13:33,688 --> 00:13:34,688
Barry called me.

226
00:13:35,527 --> 00:13:39,127
He decided to add Zhao Mei
to the shortlist for Sales Director too.

227
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:41,328
Is the list long?

228
00:13:42,328 --> 00:13:43,487
Only three people so far.

229
00:13:43,487 --> 00:13:44,968
You, Zhao Mei, and Tang Lide.

230
00:13:45,808 --> 00:13:48,847
Next, the company will hire
a consulting firm to evaluate you.

231
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:50,007
Consulting firm?

232
00:13:50,448 --> 00:13:51,448
Ruijin Consulting.

233
00:13:51,448 --> 00:13:52,408
Li Dongming's company.

234
00:13:53,328 --> 00:13:54,127
Zhao Mei's husband.

235
00:13:55,328 --> 00:13:56,088
Exactly.

236
00:13:56,928 --> 00:13:58,527
He went to Shanghai to meet Barry.

237
00:13:58,847 --> 00:14:02,088
And Barry listened to him
to some extent.

238
00:14:02,288 --> 00:14:03,487
But he didn't bring Zhao Mei.

239
00:14:04,168 --> 00:14:06,568
I thought he took Zhao Mei with him.

240
00:14:07,448 --> 00:14:08,288
But he didn't.

241
00:14:09,328 --> 00:14:10,767
He was trying to avoid suspicion.

242
00:14:11,688 --> 00:14:12,408
Very possible.

243
00:14:13,048 --> 00:14:14,288
Barry has many girlfriends.

244
00:14:14,288 --> 00:14:16,568
Li Dongming might be
catering to his preferences.

245
00:14:17,208 --> 00:14:18,448
We've met a few times.

246
00:14:18,527 --> 00:14:21,208
Every time he brought
a beautiful woman along.

247
00:14:22,048 --> 00:14:22,527
Every time?

248
00:14:23,328 --> 00:14:25,088
Those beautiful women serve a purpose.

249
00:14:25,808 --> 00:14:27,208
But I never get involved with them.

250
00:14:27,647 --> 00:14:28,448
But Barry...

251
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:31,367
I don't know about him.

252
00:14:33,568 --> 00:14:35,408
Li Dongming sounds quite impressive.

253
00:14:35,847 --> 00:14:36,767
Of course, he is.

254
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:39,487
His performance at Ruijin Consulting
is top-tier.

255
00:14:40,088 --> 00:14:42,088
And he charges the highest fees.

256
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:44,247
Okay.

257
00:14:44,688 --> 00:14:46,448
Let's focus on what we should do.

258
00:14:47,527 --> 00:14:50,328
What if Barry completely
buys into Li Dongming's story

259
00:14:50,568 --> 00:14:52,568
and gives the Sales Director position
to Zhao Mei?

260
00:14:52,847 --> 00:14:54,968
Then all our efforts over this time
would be wasted.

261
00:14:57,408 --> 00:14:59,448
Every room gets good natural light.

262
00:15:01,647 --> 00:15:02,688
Here's the restroom.

263
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:08,527
And over here is the kitchen.

264
00:15:09,048 --> 00:15:10,688
All the necessary amenities
are included.

265
00:15:10,928 --> 00:15:11,808
Well, I don't cook.

266
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:15,408
How?

267
00:15:15,928 --> 00:15:16,607
How's this place?

268
00:15:17,568 --> 00:15:19,127
The location isn't the best,

269
00:15:19,568 --> 00:15:20,568
but it's big enough.

270
00:15:20,808 --> 00:15:21,448
This way,

271
00:15:21,448 --> 00:15:22,408
I can host parties

272
00:15:22,408 --> 00:15:23,688
at home instead of outside.

273
00:15:25,688 --> 00:15:27,688
I don't understand
why you want to rent a place.

274
00:15:28,448 --> 00:15:29,727
Because I can't afford to buy.

275
00:15:30,048 --> 00:15:31,688
I don't want to live in Tianyue Garden.

276
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:33,408
I've finally realized

277
00:15:33,448 --> 00:15:35,088
as long as I live in his property

278
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:37,328
and his name is on the deed,

279
00:15:37,527 --> 00:15:39,168
I have to listen to him.

280
00:15:39,448 --> 00:15:40,168
I'm leaving him.

281
00:15:40,808 --> 00:15:42,808
The first step
is to move out of his house.

282
00:15:45,568 --> 00:15:46,527
This place is huge.

283
00:15:46,527 --> 00:15:47,367
Rent is high, I bet.

284
00:15:47,808 --> 00:15:48,607
26,000 yuan a month.

285
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:50,928
Miss,

286
00:15:52,647 --> 00:15:53,688
do you have 26,000 yuan?

287
00:15:54,048 --> 00:15:54,847
I don't.

288
00:15:56,328 --> 00:15:58,448
But since I'm moving out,

289
00:15:58,808 --> 00:16:00,928
I can't use his money for rent.

290
00:16:01,968 --> 00:16:04,127
But I've figured it out.

291
00:16:04,688 --> 00:16:06,688
Well, since I'm moving out,

292
00:16:06,847 --> 00:16:09,007
you'll naturally come live with me.

293
00:16:09,607 --> 00:16:10,487
That way,

294
00:16:10,487 --> 00:16:13,928
we can rent out your apartment
in Tianyue Garden

295
00:16:14,288 --> 00:16:16,288
and use that rent
to pay for this place's rent.

296
00:16:16,647 --> 00:16:17,247
I've checked.

297
00:16:17,527 --> 00:16:18,847
Yours can fetch 20,000 yuan.

298
00:16:19,328 --> 00:16:21,048
So we just need to add 6,000 yuan.

299
00:16:24,288 --> 00:16:24,847
Live with you?

300
00:16:27,288 --> 00:16:28,568
You said you'll live with me?

301
00:16:30,688 --> 00:16:32,208
What? Don't you want to?

302
00:16:33,208 --> 00:16:34,288
I do,

303
00:16:34,288 --> 00:16:37,688
but are you sure
you can cut ties with your dad?

304
00:16:38,448 --> 00:16:39,688
Not just the house.

305
00:16:41,328 --> 00:16:42,007
You're right.

306
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:43,527
I have to pay for

307
00:16:43,808 --> 00:16:45,048
a housekeeper and others.

308
00:16:47,568 --> 00:16:48,247
How about this?

309
00:16:48,607 --> 00:16:50,048
A chance for you. I'll live off you.

310
00:16:51,088 --> 00:16:51,808
Okay, I can.

311
00:16:52,048 --> 00:16:53,808
But we're back to that problem.

312
00:16:54,208 --> 00:16:54,808
You know,

313
00:16:54,808 --> 00:16:57,048
most of my income comes from your dad,

314
00:16:57,048 --> 00:16:59,168
so I have to rely on him, understand?

315
00:17:00,408 --> 00:17:02,088
My dad again, it's always him!

316
00:17:02,568 --> 00:17:03,647
Just switch your job.

317
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:05,287
I've hated your job for ages.

318
00:17:05,287 --> 00:17:06,448
With so many social events.

319
00:17:06,928 --> 00:17:08,928
My dad was quite decent

320
00:17:08,928 --> 00:17:11,327
before he degraded
and became a womanizer.

321
00:17:11,928 --> 00:17:13,128
Listen to me, switch your job.

322
00:17:13,287 --> 00:17:14,527
What for?

323
00:17:14,527 --> 00:17:15,648
I am a salesman.

324
00:17:15,648 --> 00:17:17,327
I'll still be a salesman anywhere else

325
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:18,247
and has social events.

326
00:17:18,448 --> 00:17:20,007
But I don't want you to be like this.

327
00:17:20,007 --> 00:17:21,168
You don't want to?

328
00:17:23,448 --> 00:17:26,128
Then let's go back and try it out first.

329
00:17:26,968 --> 00:17:28,047
If you're not okay with it,

330
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,527
then we'll do it your way.

331
00:17:33,807 --> 00:17:34,968
We're going to live together,

332
00:17:35,727 --> 00:17:36,888
but I need my own space.

333
00:17:37,208 --> 00:17:38,247
I need my own bedroom.

334
00:17:39,448 --> 00:17:41,208
Deal. The master bedroom is yours.

335
00:17:41,608 --> 00:17:42,007
Okay.

336
00:17:42,487 --> 00:17:43,968
Where's the housekeeper's room?

337
00:17:45,047 --> 00:17:46,168
I wanted to tell you that.

338
00:17:46,168 --> 00:17:48,928
My income only covers
our basic daily expenses,

339
00:17:48,928 --> 00:17:50,047
like food and drinks.

340
00:17:50,047 --> 00:17:52,047
I really can't afford a housekeeper.

341
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:53,688
What am I supposed to do without her?

342
00:17:53,807 --> 00:17:54,807
How will I get food?

343
00:17:54,807 --> 00:17:56,007
Expect me to do my laundry?

344
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,824
(Moss Cafe)

345
00:18:17,087 --> 00:18:18,487
A fresh batch of coffee beans.

346
00:18:18,807 --> 00:18:20,128
They have rich grease.

347
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:22,128
Here, try it.

348
00:18:28,688 --> 00:18:29,208
How is it?

349
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:30,208
It's delicious.

350
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:33,208
What's wrong?

351
00:18:33,727 --> 00:18:35,168
Is something bothering you?

352
00:18:36,848 --> 00:18:38,047
Is it that obvious?

353
00:18:38,848 --> 00:18:40,087
Don't even have to guess.

354
00:18:40,807 --> 00:18:42,408
If nothing were on your mind,

355
00:18:42,408 --> 00:18:45,208
you would be out visiting stores
at this hour.

356
00:18:49,168 --> 00:18:50,168
Something's on my mind,

357
00:18:50,168 --> 00:18:50,848
but

358
00:18:52,327 --> 00:18:53,047
on second thought,

359
00:18:53,047 --> 00:18:53,767
I feel

360
00:18:54,928 --> 00:18:55,448
it's nothing.

361
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:02,287
I think

362
00:19:02,648 --> 00:19:04,567
life is like this.

363
00:19:05,527 --> 00:19:06,527
At first,

364
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:09,047
it seems so unbearable.

365
00:19:10,168 --> 00:19:11,168
But after second thought,

366
00:19:12,487 --> 00:19:13,767
you're still alive, aren't you?

367
00:19:19,688 --> 00:19:20,872
I went to Shanghai yesterday.

368
00:19:21,287 --> 00:19:22,247
Shanghai?

369
00:19:23,448 --> 00:19:25,047
I quite like Shanghai.

370
00:19:25,208 --> 00:19:25,888
It's beautiful

371
00:19:26,287 --> 00:19:28,247
with lots of delicious foods.

372
00:19:29,128 --> 00:19:30,408
Why didn't you stay longer?

373
00:19:32,888 --> 00:19:33,968
I was on a business trip.

374
00:19:34,567 --> 00:19:36,007
Business trip?

375
00:19:36,168 --> 00:19:38,007
That must be a special business trip.

376
00:19:38,247 --> 00:19:40,287
Otherwise,
you wouldn't have brought it up.

377
00:19:55,608 --> 00:19:56,688
Available now?

378
00:19:57,848 --> 00:19:58,327
Yes.

379
00:20:03,272 --> 00:20:03,880
Hi.

380
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:05,788
Hi.

381
00:20:14,688 --> 00:20:15,287
Feeling better?

382
00:20:16,128 --> 00:20:16,807
Much better.

383
00:20:18,448 --> 00:20:19,336
When did you get back?

384
00:20:20,368 --> 00:20:21,487
This morning.

385
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:24,128
I planned to go to the office,

386
00:20:24,727 --> 00:20:25,968
but I was just too tired.

387
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:27,247
So I went home and slept

388
00:20:27,848 --> 00:20:29,007
straight through until 8 PM.

389
00:20:32,767 --> 00:20:33,567
You...

390
00:20:35,287 --> 00:20:35,888
Go ahead.

391
00:20:37,368 --> 00:20:38,128
No offend.

392
00:20:38,128 --> 00:20:39,128
I really wonder

393
00:20:40,087 --> 00:20:41,352
if you confronted your husband.

394
00:20:44,087 --> 00:20:45,208
It's really offensive.

395
00:20:47,608 --> 00:20:49,408
He doesn't know that I know it.

396
00:20:50,287 --> 00:20:50,968
A cool head.

397
00:20:51,888 --> 00:20:53,448
Then I underwent a fever.

398
00:20:53,928 --> 00:20:54,487
But honestly,

399
00:20:54,487 --> 00:20:55,608
I really didn't expect

400
00:20:56,688 --> 00:20:57,567
you'd act like that.

401
00:20:58,567 --> 00:21:01,087
On the flight back,
I thought my mind would race.

402
00:21:01,087 --> 00:21:02,567
But actually, nothing's on my mind.

403
00:21:04,007 --> 00:21:04,968
On the plane,

404
00:21:04,968 --> 00:21:06,408
I watched the clouds outside.

405
00:21:07,408 --> 00:21:09,087
Everything felt like a dream,

406
00:21:09,087 --> 00:21:10,168
so unreal.

407
00:21:12,287 --> 00:21:13,287
Especially...

408
00:21:21,047 --> 00:21:24,608
Especially the fact that I'm talking
to you about my husband's affair.

409
00:21:26,168 --> 00:21:26,968
We're friends.

410
00:21:31,487 --> 00:21:32,168
Down to business.

411
00:21:36,368 --> 00:21:38,128
I have a request.

412
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:39,608
Go on.

413
00:21:41,968 --> 00:21:45,327
I want you to keep this a secret.

414
00:21:46,968 --> 00:21:50,128
So you are not going to confront him.

415
00:21:51,208 --> 00:21:53,087
I told you I haven't decided yet.

416
00:21:56,247 --> 00:21:57,128
Sorry. Don't worry.

417
00:21:57,368 --> 00:22:00,168
I won't tell anyone about this.

418
00:22:01,848 --> 00:22:02,448
Thank you.

419
00:22:03,608 --> 00:22:04,448
I'll leave then.

420
00:22:05,608 --> 00:22:06,567
I don't want to meddle,

421
00:22:06,567 --> 00:22:07,168
but...

422
00:22:11,287 --> 00:22:12,567
occasionally I think to myself,

423
00:22:13,448 --> 00:22:14,287
sometimes

424
00:22:15,408 --> 00:22:16,567
I may act with ration,

425
00:22:18,247 --> 00:22:19,368
but it's just a compromise.

426
00:22:21,168 --> 00:22:22,527
Why are you telling me this?

427
00:22:24,087 --> 00:22:26,087
Just promise me you'll keep it a secret.

428
00:22:27,527 --> 00:22:28,168
I'm leaving.

429
00:22:28,408 --> 00:22:28,648
Okay.

430
00:22:43,487 --> 00:22:44,608
Mom, why didn't you pick up?

431
00:22:45,648 --> 00:22:47,327
I was dancing just now. Didn't hear it.

432
00:22:48,208 --> 00:22:48,527
Okay.

433
00:22:48,527 --> 00:22:49,807
Just wondered how you've been.

434
00:22:50,448 --> 00:22:51,208
I'm fine.

435
00:22:51,688 --> 00:22:52,487
Everything's fine.

436
00:22:52,928 --> 00:22:54,527
It's just my back acting up a bit.

437
00:22:54,928 --> 00:22:56,247
I can't do several moves.

438
00:22:56,527 --> 00:22:57,087
Back hurts?

439
00:22:57,087 --> 00:22:58,327
Yet you still pound rice cakes?

440
00:22:58,688 --> 00:22:59,247
Stop that.

441
00:22:59,727 --> 00:23:01,007
I don't do it often.

442
00:23:01,168 --> 00:23:02,527
Only once or twice a year.

443
00:23:02,608 --> 00:23:03,727
You love eating them.

444
00:23:03,928 --> 00:23:04,928
Mom, do you think

445
00:23:04,928 --> 00:23:07,368
I would like you to pound rice cakes

446
00:23:07,368 --> 00:23:08,648
regardless of your aching back?

447
00:23:08,648 --> 00:23:09,928
How could I possibly eat them?

448
00:23:10,168 --> 00:23:11,767
Stop doing such things
under the pretense

449
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:13,087
of pleasing me, okay?

450
00:23:13,208 --> 00:23:13,767
Listen.

451
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:15,287
If you make them only because of me,

452
00:23:15,287 --> 00:23:16,448
then I don't like them.

453
00:23:16,448 --> 00:23:17,247
Don't make them.

454
00:23:17,648 --> 00:23:18,608
Fine, I'll stop.

455
00:23:18,888 --> 00:23:21,408
Don't ever bother calling
to check on me either.

456
00:23:21,848 --> 00:23:23,208
Just focus on your own life.

457
00:23:23,727 --> 00:23:25,688
Anyway, you've got your place
and a girlfriend

458
00:23:25,848 --> 00:23:26,688
in Guangzhou now.

459
00:23:26,888 --> 00:23:28,408
Though we didn't help much,

460
00:23:28,527 --> 00:23:29,968
we covered the down payment, right?

461
00:23:30,208 --> 00:23:31,688
Your dad and I aren't capable people,

462
00:23:31,688 --> 00:23:32,888
but we did try our best.

463
00:23:33,408 --> 00:23:35,368
Just live your own life well.

464
00:23:35,928 --> 00:23:36,567
Let me tell you,

465
00:23:36,727 --> 00:23:39,007
we'll never be a burden to you.

466
00:23:39,168 --> 00:23:40,928
Did I ever say you were a burden?

467
00:23:41,888 --> 00:23:44,128
Wait, I'm just worried about you.

468
00:23:44,128 --> 00:23:45,208
Your back aches.

469
00:23:45,208 --> 00:23:46,247
Why say so?

470
00:23:49,007 --> 00:23:49,487
Listen.

471
00:23:50,168 --> 00:23:51,807
You come to Guangzhou next month.

472
00:23:52,087 --> 00:23:54,327
I'll get you an expert to
check your back. How's that?

473
00:23:54,767 --> 00:23:57,247
Don't bother. I'm busy now. Talk later.

474
00:24:02,928 --> 00:24:04,168
Do you know how my mom died?

475
00:24:07,928 --> 00:24:09,192
Triple-negative breast cancer.

476
00:24:10,007 --> 00:24:10,952
Out of anger to my dad.

477
00:24:12,527 --> 00:24:13,848
On this very day 12 years ago,

478
00:24:14,208 --> 00:24:16,087
I watched her take her last breath.

479
00:24:17,448 --> 00:24:19,608
My dad was in Macau, China,
only returned the next day.

480
00:24:21,007 --> 00:24:22,448
During the memorial speech for her,

481
00:24:22,888 --> 00:24:24,527
he even faked crying for a while.

482
00:24:25,287 --> 00:24:26,208
But I knew

483
00:24:27,208 --> 00:24:30,848
his mistress was waiting
in the crematorium's parking lot.

484
00:24:31,087 --> 00:24:33,007
Wait, you're meeting your father soon.

485
00:24:33,648 --> 00:24:36,072
It's your mom's death anniversary.
Let's not mention it now.

486
00:24:36,688 --> 00:24:38,527
Why do you always defend him

487
00:24:38,527 --> 00:24:39,848
whenever I criticize him?

488
00:24:40,368 --> 00:24:41,608
Can you show some backbone?

489
00:24:42,487 --> 00:24:44,928
And that sales lady under you
is hitting on my dad.

490
00:24:44,928 --> 00:24:45,688
Think I don't know?

491
00:24:47,208 --> 00:24:47,888
Sales lady?

492
00:24:48,287 --> 00:24:49,727
How many sales ladies under you?

493
00:24:49,727 --> 00:24:50,767
That Liang woman.

494
00:24:51,487 --> 00:24:52,608
Flirting shamelessly.

495
00:24:53,287 --> 00:24:54,208
First she seduced Jin,

496
00:24:54,368 --> 00:24:55,608
got bitten by his wife's dog.

497
00:24:55,888 --> 00:24:56,888
Now she targets my dad.

498
00:24:56,928 --> 00:24:59,087
Don't spread rumors without solid proof.

499
00:25:00,527 --> 00:25:02,287
Why do I need solid proof for this?

500
00:25:02,527 --> 00:25:04,567
I've seen too many women like that
around my dad.

501
00:25:04,848 --> 00:25:06,087
At least half a dozen.

502
00:25:06,368 --> 00:25:07,448
Those sales ladies

503
00:25:07,448 --> 00:25:08,527
are all gold diggers.

504
00:25:12,487 --> 00:25:14,527
Pull over!

505
00:25:18,527 --> 00:25:19,128
It's not far.

506
00:25:19,128 --> 00:25:19,928
I'll walk there.

507
00:25:20,128 --> 00:25:20,888
Don't follow me.

508
00:25:25,928 --> 00:25:26,608
What's wrong?

509
00:25:57,688 --> 00:25:58,848
No matter what you think,

510
00:26:00,247 --> 00:26:03,087
let's just call a truce today.

511
00:26:04,848 --> 00:26:05,527
Let's go eat.

512
00:26:18,888 --> 00:26:20,727
The chef makes
decent Sichuan cuisine now.

513
00:26:22,448 --> 00:26:23,807
He doesn't know that.

514
00:26:24,368 --> 00:26:26,168
He even gets worse
on his Cantonese cuisine.

515
00:26:26,648 --> 00:26:28,688
His cooking has been bland lately.

516
00:26:29,327 --> 00:26:29,928
So,

517
00:26:29,928 --> 00:26:32,327
I hired a chef from Lanzhizhai
to cook here.

518
00:26:32,527 --> 00:26:33,648
Come on, try it!

519
00:26:33,928 --> 00:26:36,368
Lanzhizhai is popular now.
Takes a month to reserve.

520
00:26:37,007 --> 00:26:38,287
It's all hype.

521
00:26:40,168 --> 00:26:42,608
I remembered when I first made money,

522
00:26:42,928 --> 00:26:43,648
I had a dream

523
00:26:44,608 --> 00:26:47,087
of having two chefs at home,

524
00:26:48,047 --> 00:26:49,087
one Cantonese,

525
00:26:49,287 --> 00:26:50,247
and one Sichuanese.

526
00:26:51,007 --> 00:26:53,608
Now I realize that dream was pointless.

527
00:26:54,727 --> 00:26:56,807
Nowadays, be it eight major cuisines,

528
00:26:57,448 --> 00:26:58,688
Italian or French cuisine,

529
00:26:59,247 --> 00:27:02,688
with money, you can hire any chef
to cook for you.

530
00:27:03,448 --> 00:27:05,047
If you dislike it or get bored,

531
00:27:05,888 --> 00:27:06,688
change the chef.

532
00:27:07,608 --> 00:27:09,128
No need to keep a private chef.

533
00:27:09,848 --> 00:27:10,928
Same goes to other things.

534
00:27:11,487 --> 00:27:12,767
Want to play tennis?

535
00:27:12,767 --> 00:27:13,688
Find a tennis coach.

536
00:27:14,408 --> 00:27:15,327
Want to play golf?

537
00:27:15,487 --> 00:27:16,487
Find a golf coach.

538
00:27:17,007 --> 00:27:17,807
Everything's there.

539
00:27:18,608 --> 00:27:20,648
These are all benefits
brought by social progress.

540
00:27:22,848 --> 00:27:23,688
Exactly.

541
00:27:24,688 --> 00:27:26,688
Want bigger eyes? Just go find a girl.

542
00:27:26,928 --> 00:27:28,527
Want fairer skin? Just find another.

543
00:27:29,608 --> 00:27:32,287
No, this has nothing to do
with social progress.

544
00:27:32,727 --> 00:27:33,527
It's about money.

545
00:27:34,487 --> 00:27:35,784
You know it better than anyone.

546
00:27:36,448 --> 00:27:37,007
Rice cakes.

547
00:27:37,727 --> 00:27:38,327
Enjoy.

548
00:27:39,087 --> 00:27:39,888
Rice cakes.

549
00:27:40,567 --> 00:27:43,047
Dong Yue, you have a special connection
with these rice cakes.

550
00:27:43,527 --> 00:27:44,168
What connection?

551
00:27:45,047 --> 00:27:46,368
Dong Yue's Ma makes rice cakes.

552
00:27:46,448 --> 00:27:47,408
She mailed them to him.

553
00:27:47,567 --> 00:27:49,848
He even scolded his Ma
over the phone earlier.

554
00:27:50,688 --> 00:27:51,727
Mom, not Ma.

555
00:27:52,807 --> 00:27:53,567
Language.

556
00:27:54,368 --> 00:27:56,727
Mr. Shen, my mom has back problems,

557
00:27:57,208 --> 00:27:58,767
so I told her

558
00:27:59,487 --> 00:28:01,047
to stop making rice cakes.

559
00:28:03,128 --> 00:28:03,688
I was worried

560
00:28:03,968 --> 00:28:05,448
and sounded harsh.

561
00:28:06,688 --> 00:28:08,408
I plan to bring her to Guangzhou soon

562
00:28:08,848 --> 00:28:09,527
to see an expert.

563
00:28:12,208 --> 00:28:13,448
Try physical therapy.

564
00:28:14,128 --> 00:28:15,688
I know a good doctor.

565
00:28:16,648 --> 00:28:17,888
Last time, a friend of mine

566
00:28:18,327 --> 00:28:19,608
had bone spurs on his spine

567
00:28:20,208 --> 00:28:21,807
and recovered through physical therapy.

568
00:28:24,047 --> 00:28:24,767
Bring your mother

569
00:28:24,888 --> 00:28:25,487
to him.

570
00:28:26,648 --> 00:28:27,007
Thanks.

571
00:28:28,168 --> 00:28:28,567
Wait.

572
00:28:29,807 --> 00:28:31,087
Are you bringing your mom here?

573
00:28:31,888 --> 00:28:32,727
What do you mean?

574
00:28:33,368 --> 00:28:34,368
That's Dong Yue's mother.

575
00:28:34,807 --> 00:28:35,720
He can bring her here.

576
00:28:36,128 --> 00:28:37,888
She can come,
but no staying at your place.

577
00:28:38,247 --> 00:28:38,727
Why?

578
00:28:39,807 --> 00:28:40,928
Because I'll go over.

579
00:28:40,928 --> 00:28:42,527
How awkward with your mom around.

580
00:28:43,648 --> 00:28:44,208
Listen,

581
00:28:44,648 --> 00:28:45,928
I'll book her a luxury hotel.

582
00:28:46,128 --> 00:28:46,487
Shut up!

583
00:28:49,727 --> 00:28:50,848
That's Dong Yue's place.

584
00:28:53,368 --> 00:28:54,727
Well, I'll handle this.

585
00:28:55,807 --> 00:28:57,688
I'll schedule an appointment
with the doctor

586
00:28:57,848 --> 00:28:58,408
and send a car

587
00:28:58,968 --> 00:28:59,888
to pick up your mother.

588
00:29:00,608 --> 00:29:02,128
That way, she won't suffer the trip.

589
00:29:03,128 --> 00:29:03,767
Thank you.

590
00:29:05,408 --> 00:29:06,688
You're so corny.

591
00:29:07,047 --> 00:29:08,408
Listen, without my permission,

592
00:29:08,408 --> 00:29:09,368
don't go wild. Got it?

593
00:29:17,408 --> 00:29:18,007
Finished?

594
00:29:19,287 --> 00:29:19,848
What's wrong?

595
00:29:21,727 --> 00:29:22,287
You stay.

596
00:29:23,928 --> 00:29:25,608
Come with me. I need to talk to you.

597
00:29:39,608 --> 00:29:39,848
Sit.

598
00:29:41,848 --> 00:29:42,487
No thanks.

599
00:29:42,688 --> 00:29:44,368
Get to the point please.

600
00:29:48,608 --> 00:29:50,087
I heard you've been partying wildly.

601
00:29:51,128 --> 00:29:51,888
Don't deny it.

602
00:29:52,648 --> 00:29:54,648
I know all about you.

603
00:29:56,128 --> 00:29:57,368
Of course, you do.

604
00:29:57,527 --> 00:29:59,848
Is there anything in Guangzhou
you don't know?

605
00:30:00,487 --> 00:30:01,368
Since I know,

606
00:30:01,888 --> 00:30:03,487
Dong Yue must know too.

607
00:30:03,727 --> 00:30:04,567
So what?

608
00:30:04,968 --> 00:30:06,608
I haven't done anything inappropriate.

609
00:30:06,608 --> 00:30:08,848
Just some singing and drinking,

610
00:30:08,848 --> 00:30:09,767
having fun.

611
00:30:10,767 --> 00:30:12,448
He also has social events every night.

612
00:30:12,448 --> 00:30:13,688
Why should I stay at home?

613
00:30:13,688 --> 00:30:14,567
You know nothing.

614
00:30:15,087 --> 00:30:16,208
Social events?

615
00:30:17,368 --> 00:30:19,087
It is normal for him
in the liquor business.

616
00:30:20,168 --> 00:30:20,807
Don't you know?

617
00:30:22,327 --> 00:30:24,047
Dong Yue is always sober.

618
00:30:25,247 --> 00:30:25,968
From what I know,

619
00:30:26,448 --> 00:30:28,608
he's never crossed any lines.

620
00:30:29,807 --> 00:30:31,128
Among all the salespeople,

621
00:30:31,448 --> 00:30:33,087
he's the most principled one.

622
00:30:33,087 --> 00:30:35,208
Yet you keep pushing boundaries.

623
00:30:35,968 --> 00:30:37,047
What do you mean?

624
00:30:37,487 --> 00:30:38,448
Like you said,

625
00:30:38,448 --> 00:30:40,247
I'm just having fun. Same as you.

626
00:30:40,368 --> 00:30:40,928
Having fun?

627
00:30:41,608 --> 00:30:42,408
What about that guy?

628
00:30:43,087 --> 00:30:43,888
Daniel, right?

629
00:30:46,168 --> 00:30:48,767
I've already told his boss to fire him.

630
00:30:48,968 --> 00:30:49,807
Why?

631
00:30:49,928 --> 00:30:51,007
How dare you fire him?

632
00:30:51,087 --> 00:30:52,128
Because I'm your father.

633
00:30:53,608 --> 00:30:54,567
I don't understand.

634
00:30:55,208 --> 00:30:57,247
You've been raised in such privilege.

635
00:30:57,448 --> 00:30:59,527
How could you possibly
be interested in that man?

636
00:30:59,807 --> 00:31:01,408
And you even fought for his favor?

637
00:31:02,688 --> 00:31:04,087
You are my daughter.

638
00:31:04,928 --> 00:31:06,527
Don't be so shallow.

639
00:31:07,928 --> 00:31:08,848
Shallow? Me?

640
00:31:09,287 --> 00:31:10,408
Then who's classy?

641
00:31:11,168 --> 00:31:12,767
The hostesses at Cocoon

642
00:31:13,128 --> 00:31:14,527
or that sales lady bitten by a dog?

643
00:31:14,527 --> 00:31:16,087
I don't care if you get it.

644
00:31:16,567 --> 00:31:18,287
If I hear you're running wild again,

645
00:31:18,368 --> 00:31:19,608
I'll show no mercy.

646
00:31:19,928 --> 00:31:20,448
Wait, Dad.

647
00:31:20,448 --> 00:31:21,688
She just wouldn't listen to me.

648
00:31:23,247 --> 00:31:25,007
Don't just lecture me. Go talk to her.

649
00:31:25,287 --> 00:31:26,247
I was just worried.

650
00:31:27,487 --> 00:31:29,087
Don't you know your mom?

651
00:31:29,487 --> 00:31:30,408
She has her pride.

652
00:31:30,888 --> 00:31:32,648
Call her later to make her happy.

653
00:31:33,368 --> 00:31:34,247
Tell your mom

654
00:31:34,848 --> 00:31:36,487
you'll take her
to a doctor in Guangzhou.

655
00:31:36,487 --> 00:31:38,648
Actually, we've seen a doctor last week.

656
00:31:39,087 --> 00:31:39,648
What?

657
00:31:41,327 --> 00:31:42,928
She didn't mean to hide it from you.

658
00:31:43,527 --> 00:31:45,688
She just doesn't know
how to talk to you right now.

659
00:31:46,168 --> 00:31:46,727
Understood?

660
00:31:47,648 --> 00:31:49,168
She didn't want me to tell you,

661
00:31:49,848 --> 00:31:50,888
but I thought about it

662
00:31:51,128 --> 00:31:52,208
and decided to tell you,

663
00:31:52,487 --> 00:31:53,448
so you wouldn't worry.

664
00:31:54,527 --> 00:31:56,208
Anyway, rest assured.

665
00:31:57,128 --> 00:31:58,087
We've seen a doctor.

666
00:31:59,007 --> 00:31:59,928
Okay, Dad. Gotta go.

667
00:32:01,448 --> 00:32:01,968
Let's go.

668
00:32:02,688 --> 00:32:04,247
I've severed my ties with Shen Mo.

669
00:32:04,327 --> 00:32:05,247
What are you doing?

670
00:32:05,688 --> 00:32:06,448
Want to stay?

671
00:32:07,287 --> 00:32:08,247
You have two choices.

672
00:32:08,247 --> 00:32:09,807
Cut ties with him or break up with me.

673
00:32:09,807 --> 00:32:10,807
Choose. Right now.

674
00:32:11,047 --> 00:32:12,888
Ignore her. She's losing a temper.

675
00:32:13,128 --> 00:32:14,327
You're insane! Crazy!

676
00:32:14,648 --> 00:32:15,448
Break up.

677
00:32:18,368 --> 00:32:18,928
What?

678
00:32:18,928 --> 00:32:19,567
Say that again.

679
00:32:23,848 --> 00:32:24,688
Let's break up.

680
00:32:24,688 --> 00:32:25,848
We're not a good match.

681
00:32:26,247 --> 00:32:27,448
You piece of trash!

682
00:32:27,848 --> 00:32:28,448
Just stay here

683
00:32:28,448 --> 00:32:30,007
and go die with this piece of trash!

684
00:32:36,368 --> 00:32:38,527
Liu, Xing just ran out.

685
00:32:39,087 --> 00:32:39,848
Keep an eye on her.

686
00:32:44,208 --> 00:32:46,168
Leave her be. She always acts like this.

687
00:32:46,608 --> 00:32:47,968
Come here. I need to talk to you.

688
00:32:48,767 --> 00:32:49,448
Shen Xing

689
00:32:49,648 --> 00:32:50,767
is reckless with her words.

690
00:32:51,888 --> 00:32:53,807
Don't take what she says too seriously.

691
00:32:55,448 --> 00:32:57,888
Young couples
inevitably clash sometimes.

692
00:32:59,608 --> 00:33:00,287
Down to business.

693
00:33:01,487 --> 00:33:02,928
I had someone investigate Zhao Mei.

694
00:33:04,448 --> 00:33:06,128
She's the head of Promotions Department.

695
00:33:07,087 --> 00:33:10,128
What's your company's
annual promotions budget?

696
00:33:10,807 --> 00:33:11,327
30 million?

697
00:33:11,928 --> 00:33:12,527
50 million?

698
00:33:13,888 --> 00:33:14,968
This year it's 55 million.

699
00:33:15,327 --> 00:33:16,208
Exactly.

700
00:33:17,648 --> 00:33:21,168
Think about how much Xu Yuntian
has embezzled over his years at GST.

701
00:33:22,968 --> 00:33:25,567
Zhao Mei was handpicked by him.

702
00:33:26,888 --> 00:33:29,208
She handles tens of millions
in promotions funds

703
00:33:29,208 --> 00:33:30,128
every year,

704
00:33:30,767 --> 00:33:31,848
so she can't be clean.

705
00:33:33,888 --> 00:33:34,727
As for Barry,

706
00:33:35,408 --> 00:33:36,727
he's a total fence-sitter.

707
00:33:37,408 --> 00:33:38,287
He's unreliable.

708
00:33:39,007 --> 00:33:40,487
We need to give this a push.

709
00:33:42,448 --> 00:33:45,928
Once we have financial dirt on Zhao Mei,

710
00:33:46,727 --> 00:33:49,208
forget about becoming Sales Director,

711
00:33:50,087 --> 00:33:52,448
she won't even keep
her Deputy Director position.

712
00:33:52,448 --> 00:33:52,888
Mr. Shen.

713
00:33:56,087 --> 00:33:59,727
I meant it when I said to break up
with Shen Xing.

714
00:34:04,727 --> 00:34:07,208
You're GST's largest distributor,

715
00:34:09,687 --> 00:34:12,687
also my most crucial client.

716
00:34:14,888 --> 00:34:15,808
But no matter what,

717
00:34:18,127 --> 00:34:19,328
I must break up with her.

718
00:34:24,768 --> 00:34:25,288
Sorry.

719
00:34:37,968 --> 00:34:39,567
(I think I'm truly not a decent person.)

720
00:34:40,848 --> 00:34:41,687
(I thought about)

721
00:34:42,007 --> 00:34:43,187
(breaking up with Shen Xing)

722
00:34:43,187 --> 00:34:44,968
(when I learned
she is Shen Mo's daughter.)

723
00:34:46,167 --> 00:34:47,567
(Yet I only said it today.)

724
00:34:49,728 --> 00:34:52,712
(When Shen Mo tried to convince me,
I thought about taking my words back.)

725
00:34:53,527 --> 00:34:54,768
(But I didn't.)

726
00:34:57,007 --> 00:34:57,832
(I couldn't do it.)

727
00:35:00,007 --> 00:35:02,448
(Actually, if I kept dating Shen Xing,)

728
00:35:02,448 --> 00:35:04,007
(then I would degrade myself further)

729
00:35:05,448 --> 00:35:06,448
(to a shameless man.)

730
00:35:08,687 --> 00:35:10,047
(Shen Mo would look down on me,)

731
00:35:11,087 --> 00:35:12,647
(even I'd look down on myself.)

732
00:35:55,271 --> 00:35:57,768
(Zhao Mei)

733
00:36:22,808 --> 00:36:24,047
(There were countless moments)

734
00:36:24,487 --> 00:36:26,328
(I almost called Li Dongming)

735
00:36:27,087 --> 00:36:27,848
(to tell him,)

736
00:36:28,167 --> 00:36:29,968
("Li Dongming, I know everything.")

737
00:36:31,087 --> 00:36:32,607
(Jia Le Cafe)
(How satisfying it would be.)

738
00:36:33,968 --> 00:36:35,368
(But as an employee, I can't.)

739
00:36:36,248 --> 00:36:38,647
(Try telling others
about your husband's affair.)

740
00:36:39,007 --> 00:36:41,207
(See if your boss and colleagues
will support you.)

741
00:36:42,408 --> 00:36:43,888
(Fighting alone in society,)

742
00:36:44,087 --> 00:36:44,888
(I have to learn)

743
00:36:45,087 --> 00:36:46,487
(Connie, Ruijin Consulting)
(to endure and read the room.)

744
00:36:46,487 --> 00:36:47,687
(Senior Analyst, Executive Coach)
(Otherwise, I'd only suffer)

745
00:36:47,888 --> 00:36:48,968
(and get seriously hurt.)

746
00:36:49,087 --> 00:36:50,567
(No one will pity on me.)

747
00:36:50,888 --> 00:36:51,848
This is you.

748
00:36:52,567 --> 00:36:54,368
This ladder is your career.

749
00:36:54,647 --> 00:36:57,567
You climb up diligently every day.

750
00:36:58,248 --> 00:36:59,647
Suppose this is promotions.

751
00:37:00,207 --> 00:37:02,487
Then the Sales Director would be here.

752
00:37:03,808 --> 00:37:04,248
Right.

753
00:37:05,007 --> 00:37:07,848
Actually, becoming Sales Director
is a career shift for me.

754
00:37:08,288 --> 00:37:09,487
I've never done sales.

755
00:37:10,368 --> 00:37:11,808
That's what stresses me most.

756
00:37:17,728 --> 00:37:18,368
What about this?

757
00:37:22,647 --> 00:37:23,808
From this perspective,

758
00:37:25,567 --> 00:37:27,167
there are many ways to go.

759
00:37:28,207 --> 00:37:29,728
Yes, look.

760
00:37:30,047 --> 00:37:32,167
This is a grid framework.

761
00:37:32,487 --> 00:37:33,448
You can move upward,

762
00:37:34,207 --> 00:37:35,888
go left or right.

763
00:37:36,167 --> 00:37:37,808
You can even circle back.

764
00:37:38,487 --> 00:37:41,007
So a career isn't a ladder,

765
00:37:42,207 --> 00:37:43,127
but a grid framework.

766
00:37:43,888 --> 00:37:44,647
Exactly.

767
00:37:44,968 --> 00:37:46,408
Climbing up a ladder

768
00:37:46,808 --> 00:37:49,567
means you're always staring
at the person above you.

769
00:37:50,007 --> 00:37:52,928
But climbing up a grid framework

770
00:37:53,288 --> 00:37:54,448
gives you huge potential.

771
00:37:54,728 --> 00:37:59,167
Li Dongming asked me to train you
for this Sales Director position.

772
00:37:59,968 --> 00:38:01,968
I think that limits you too much.

773
00:38:02,207 --> 00:38:03,487
And it limits me too.

774
00:38:05,888 --> 00:38:07,207
You really cheer me up.

775
00:38:07,968 --> 00:38:09,207
You are a great teacher.

776
00:38:12,007 --> 00:38:13,127
I should thank Li Dongming.

777
00:38:14,487 --> 00:38:15,328
When he gets here,

778
00:38:15,487 --> 00:38:16,567
say it right to his face.

779
00:38:44,283 --> 00:38:49,023
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

780
00:38:53,473 --> 00:38:55,393
♪Too much of shame♪

781
00:38:55,739 --> 00:38:58,535
♪To waste it crying♪

782
00:39:00,993 --> 00:39:02,913
♪Leave all behind you♪

783
00:39:02,913 --> 00:39:05,193
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

784
00:39:05,313 --> 00:39:07,542
♪You know how far you've gone♪

785
00:39:07,677 --> 00:39:09,953
♪In the fire you rise again♪

786
00:39:10,139 --> 00:39:12,499
♪You made it through the worst♪

787
00:39:12,637 --> 00:39:14,841
♪The best is yet to come♪

788
00:39:15,084 --> 00:39:17,224
♪The best is yet to come♪

789
00:39:19,926 --> 00:39:21,249
♪Isn't it magical♪

790
00:39:21,249 --> 00:39:22,881
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

791
00:39:22,913 --> 00:39:25,380
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

792
00:39:25,380 --> 00:39:27,833
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

793
00:39:27,914 --> 00:39:30,562
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

794
00:39:30,651 --> 00:39:33,182
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

795
00:39:33,262 --> 00:39:35,484
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

796
00:39:35,626 --> 00:39:36,707
♪But I don't want to♪

797
00:39:36,816 --> 00:39:39,082
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

798
00:39:39,198 --> 00:39:40,263
♪Until 3 AM♪

799
00:39:40,434 --> 00:39:41,639
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

800
00:39:41,793 --> 00:39:43,026
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

801
00:39:43,117 --> 00:39:45,481
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

802
00:39:45,628 --> 00:39:50,038
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

803
00:40:04,763 --> 00:40:06,199
♪Leave all behind you♪

804
00:40:06,303 --> 00:40:08,790
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

805
00:40:08,973 --> 00:40:11,102
♪You know how far you've gone♪

806
00:40:11,289 --> 00:40:13,629
♪In the fire you rise again♪

807
00:40:13,697 --> 00:40:15,963
♪You made it through the worst♪

808
00:40:16,323 --> 00:40:18,401
♪The best is yet to come♪

809
00:40:18,650 --> 00:40:20,820
♪The best is yet to come♪

810
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:24,673
♪Isn't it magical♪

811
00:40:24,673 --> 00:40:28,319
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

812
00:40:28,353 --> 00:40:30,209
♪And I see them sparkling♪

813
00:40:30,433 --> 00:40:32,564
♪Nobody knows♪

814
00:40:33,185 --> 00:40:35,095
♪What tomorrow brings♪

815
00:40:35,361 --> 00:40:37,684
♪You made it through the worst♪

816
00:40:37,871 --> 00:40:40,079
♪The best is yet to come♪

817
00:40:40,366 --> 00:40:42,515
♪The best is yet to come♪

818
00:40:42,811 --> 00:40:44,225
♪Isn't it magical♪

819
00:40:44,225 --> 00:40:46,437
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

820
00:40:46,511 --> 00:40:48,865
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

821
00:40:48,865 --> 00:40:49,953
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

822
00:40:49,953 --> 00:40:53,404
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

823
00:40:53,857 --> 00:40:56,131
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

824
00:40:56,545 --> 00:40:57,409
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

825
00:40:57,409 --> 00:40:58,929
♪Isn't it magical♪
